# Festag — dark-mode CTAs

In **dark / OLED** auth and onboarding chrome, primary and ghost CTAs share one quiet slate fill until the form is ready.

## Idle (empty / invalid / not ready)

Both primary and ghost stay **darker / quieter**:

```css
background: rgba(186, 194, 210, 0.08); /* --festag-btn-dark-bg */
color: rgba(245, 245, 247, 0.88);
border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06); /* minimal white hairline */
```

Hover/active idle lifts only slightly (`0.16` / `0.22`).

## Ready (valid input → `--ready`)

Only the **primary** action lifts a clear step lighter after successful input (e.g. name filled, valid invite emails):

```css
background: rgba(186, 194, 210, 0.28); /* --festag-btn-dark-ready-bg */
color: #f5f5f7;
```

Hover `0.36`, active `0.42`. Ghost / secondary skip actions stay at idle density so the hierarchy is obvious.

## Tokens

Use `--festag-btn-dark-*` and `--festag-btn-dark-ready-*` from `components/auth/auth-chrome-tokens.ts`. Do not hardcode near-white fills or borders on dark CTAs.

## Do not

- Make idle primary and ready primary look the same
- Force `--ready` on empty invite / empty name fields
- Give ghost the ready lift (skip / secondary stays quiet)
- Reintroduce light-mode white Linear strokes into dark CTAs

See also `festag-light-mode-ctas.mdc` (light stays white fills) and `festag-auth-no-field-borders.mdc`.
